          <p>Getting an instrument rating is the next step in your training. It allows you to handle more challenging weather with proper training. Essentially, you'll learn to fly by focusing only on your flight instruments, without relying on the ground or horizon. This skill is crucial for flying in less than ideal weather conditions.</p>
          <p class="pt-10">During the process, you'll understand the rules, procedures, and the published minimums to fly safely in such conditions. It's about expanding your skills and flying confidently in more complex weather situations.</p>
